{"articles":[{"aggregator_short_tag":"Trending","aggmeta_short_tag":"Trending","aggregator_siteid":"451","aggregatorunreadcount":"58","sitegrouporder":"1","sortid":"1","short_tag":"India","article_id":"2400093","post_title":"The list is out! Meet the superstar finalists of  Global Technology Innovation Contest 2020 India!","post_content_stripped":"Yes, the moment you’ve all been waiting for is finally here, ATCI! We’ve got the names of the Global Technology Innovation Contest (GTIC) 2020 – India finalists. Let’s tip our hats to the incredible tech innovators and give them a big round of applause! These 14 teams chosen from the 86 prototypes—truly exemplify our zeal to think outside the box and innovate, both for business and society. Without further ado, let’s find out who they are. What’s more? You can take the jury’s seat and vote for your favorite innovation to help them win the People’s Choice Award! Got a personal favorite? Vote for your favorite GTIC Team or Idea: People’s Choice Award Theme: Innovate for Society Intelligent Pandemic Management Using Game Theory Problem Statement: “Every Battle is Won or Lost Before it is Ever Fought” This is the famous advice from Sun Tzu’s Art of War. The situation we are in today is no less than a war with an invisible enemy – COVID Virus. Today, the governments are struggling to manage pandemics as they do no have an efficient mechanism to strategize with limited resources and control the pandemic. Solution: We bring ‘Chanakya – An intelligent pandemic management system’ based on Game theory that anticipates the next step of the enemy and proposes next best action. Here, the infected patients are the attackers and healthcare, police and other essential support staff as defenders. Our strategy engine built using Stackelberg Game Algorithm determines the next best action based on the moves of the attacker and the payoff. Using machine learning, the game learns from past strategies and outcomes to devise new strategies. Benefit: Decision makers can now simulate strategies with Chanakya at their fingertips to make smart and quick decisions. With our system in place, we all will be better prepared for our next pandemic and save millions of lives and their livelihood. Innovators : Roshan Clive Dmello, Sweta Mahendrakar, Ashwija Shetty, Shraddha Modi and Shweta Bhanushali Posture Corrector using Deep Learning Framework Description: Ergonomics, Stress and Long Sitting (ESL) lead to poor posture and for every 60min of slouch you reduce life expectancy by 22min. Solutions for posture corrector exist but not popular as they focus on generating alerts but not on the holistic idea of managing the ESL effect through activism. This is where our cloud AI/ML based solution, “WellErt” creates a differentiation “WellErt” uses the device camera and with user consent monitors the the slouch using AI without compromising data privacy. Based on user readings the cloud ML model generates curated alerts/activities to engage the user into a cycle of activism and making upright posture a good habit Innovators : Lavanya Sripathi, Shailesh Chaphekar, Ajay Merulingkar, Ashish Saraswat and Kalyani Jadhav Unleashing the Potential of Digital Personas Situation: We need STEAM not STEM to prepare kids for 4th Industrial revolution. 13% of world’s children are underprivileged. A study by National Endowment of Arts reveals that students from low socio-economic backgrounds who participate in arts are more likely to aspire for higher education. 84 percent of elementary schools host visual arts programs and museums are recognized as parallel education systems to school . But, visits to museums are declining since 2000. Solution: A patented AI based conversational Personal Digital Twin-extending your impact across space and time. The multi-modal digital persona brings an expressive, immersive and responsive environment through Human Centred Computing. Benefit: Adhering to Accenture’s pillars of Responsible Business the immersive digital persona aims to transform art education sessions through increased learning rate by10x and enthrall the young minds during the average 300K learning sessions on art held globally every year. Innovators : Sanjay Podder, Nisha Ramachandra, Neville Dubash, Raghotham M Rao and Manish Ahuja Hide &amp; Seek Idea: Steganography is used to conceal information- a file, message, image, or video within another file, message, image, or video. Research shows steganography-based attacks have increased a 600 % in last 3 Years. This technique is extensively used by threat actors- Terrorist Organizations for communication, Corporate Espionage (Stealing sensitive information) or Hackers/Nation states for Cyber attacks. Solution: Hide and Seek, provides a unique solution to detect steganography and use of quantum computing to decipher the hidden information inside the image. Benefits: The solution offers the capability to integrate with communication channels and Cyber protection solutions for detection and to prevent compromise of business sensitive information/data. Innovators : Lakshmi Purushotham, Romesh Viswanath, Rajat Sehdev, Ram Venkatakrishnan and Deepak Sharma Carbon Intelligent Advisor Problem it Solves: Despite clearer skies and moderate traffic on roads, average per-capita carbon emissions of 13.5 kg, has not gone down. And the real culprits to carbon emissions are our food, entertainment and digital habits. We need to solve this crisis NOW. How: Go Carbon, is an Augmented Reality based Ecological Well-Being framework, that uses Gamification, which nudges the user towards changing their carbon-intensive habits to Green Habits, with subtle behavioral cues, rewards, social credit and creating a sense of larger purpose. Impact: Helping individuals, communities and organizations become responsible in the new by neutralizing one carbon score at a time. Innovators : Prerna Khurana, Dimple Walia, Banda Prasad, Vibhu Sharma and Rahul Grover Eye Ball Controlled Wheel Chair Description: “ In India One person per/min. is injured due to the Road Accidents and some of them loses their complete mobility as per the Govt Data.” People suffering from Quadriplegia or Tetraplegia loose their ability to move from one place to another due to which he/she needs to depend on others for mobility. Our solution is to build an eyeball-controlled wheelchair based on the Image processing techniques (Image Acquisition / Data Processing / Device Controller) to analyze eyeball movements and Smart Controller moves the wheelchair towards desired directions. Solution can address to the current challenges of the Quadriplegia patients or other disabilities and their care giver or family members by enabling the intelligent platform/monitoring system. No Market Player / OEMs working on such concept. Innovators : Ravi Shankar Kumar, Susanta Roy, Ajay Kumar P, Arnab Ghosh and Rangaraju Devaraju Voices Unheard: Migrant Workers in India Description: COVID-19 and lockdown has brought the grim face and sorry state of migrant workers. This is an unorganized sector of over 300M migrant workers in India. Most of them are uninsured, live under unhygienic conditions with no bright future prospect for their next generations. Their immense contributions in nation building goes unnoticed. In current crisis of Covid-19 they are the worst sufferers, and many have lost their lives and livelihood. Post Covid-19, situation remains even grim if not addressed effectively. Our solution, Sanmaan – Powered by AI, addresses the problem holistically, it leverages easy to use App for migrant workers and AI built on it to build a long term, sustainable solution for the welfare of migrant workers and growth plans for their next generations. Our vision is: AAS (meaning Hope): Apmaan (Affront) se Armaan (Aspiration) aur Sanmaan (Self-esteem) tak Innovators : Santosh Bhawar, Radhika Palanivelu, Manish K More, Maheshwar Ture and Suresh Kumar K Theme: Innovate for Business Ubiquitous Drug Discovery Description: Drug discovery is a time taking and costly endeavor. Getting a perfect molecular match which binds to a disease protein is a challenge. In our idea, we go beyond existing approved drugs molecules, to consider all/any other molecules as an input for our novel Generative AI model for recommending new drug molecular structures. We finally check if any of our generated molecules, can potentially bind to any disease target proteins. Innovators : Praveen Viswanathan, Dhruv Bajpai, Sowmya Parthasarathi, Abhilash Manu and Rohini Nagare Zero Data Breach Description: Zero Data Breach platform can help secure data while monetizing it, without losing the competitive advantage. 50% of Fortune 500 companies have had some form of a data breach. Our Innovation is to bring Clean Dataroom and secure IP Marketplace through “Zero Data Breach Platform”. The platform uses privacy-preserving techniques like homomorphic encryption, secure enclaves, and blockchain to give organizations a secure environment to share their data and algorithms in the e-commerce like marketplace. With both data and IP protected, our innovation enables clients with new revenue streams/business models. For e.g. industries like pharma and healthcare can share data to expedite their drug discovery process. Innovators : Sunil Krishnan, Deepak Lalan, Melvin Tomy, Amit Kawad and Priyanka Jain Disaster Resilient Telcom Networks Description: Wildfires causes major damage to telecom network infrastructure across the globe. The calamity also causes major disruption in communications cutting off large sections of disaster affected people without any communication for several days post the disaster. Our Innovation provides solutions to tackle two challenges. 1. Frontier is an early warning system &amp; intelligent disaster impact analysis system built on IoT, AI and Low Power Wide Area NW (LPWAN). 2. SurvivorNet – An emergency &amp; rapid communication network in the disaster affected zone using open source cellular radio base station technology and cognitive radio. This provides smart platform solutions to address Telcom &amp; similar network challenges during &amp; after disasters. The solution can focus Innovation at scale. Innovators : Ramkumar Sembaiyan, Madan Kumar, Sandeep Rajagopal, Aditya Gupta and Krishna Chaitanya Digital Rajamouli 2.0 Description: I have a dream where I want to see myself in place of Prabhas and be by the side of my crush in Bahubali. Digital Rajamouli enables the users to realize this  dream by allowing them to replace the character they fantasize, leveraging the power of Deep-Faking &amp; Artificial Intelligence. Disrupt experience of next Gen audience in multi billion-dollar sectors like Entertainment (OTT- $80bn/Year), Social media ($100+ bn/Year) and even EduTech Platforms (eg: BYJUS is expected to double its subscribers base to 100mn by 2022). Innovators : Sree Gautham Alluri, Sravani Polapally, Kavin Upadhyay, Injamuri Praveena and Polamarasetty Nirmal Voice Dubbing Model/Software Problem Statement: Dubbing industry today is heavily dependent on manual efforts from dubbing artists, script writers leading to high cost and long lead time that too with inadequate quality. Solution: Our “DubbSmart” - AI based Voice Dubbing Platform uses deep learning algorithms to analyze different aspects (tone , accent and pitch etc.) of original voice and converts it into the desired language retaining the same voice characteristics. Benefit: The solution can eliminate the huge dependency on script writers and dubbing artists providing multi-times efficiency in time to market, drastic cost reductions and can completely revolutionize the entertainment, media, e-Learning and other industries. Innovators : Aayush Raj, Varun Pratap Bhardwaj, Anvita Sharma, Kapil Sahni and Manu Bhargava Virtual Storefront Platform : A New (Extended) Reality for Retailers and Brands Challenge: With customers now quickly moving to e-commerce platforms, there is a need to revitalize luxury retail brands suffering from low footfall and dwindling sales by giving their loyal customers an immersive customer experience that would go far beyond the real-world physical shopping. Solution: Virtual Storefront platform uses Virtual Reality to teleport the customer to a desired location say a Miami beach where they can try and buy products like a swim wear and matching accessories along with sharing the shopping experience with their friends who they may not be able to meet in real life, all through the comfort of their homes. Benefits: This innovation takes a huge leap from classic ecommerce thumbnail listing, widens the product searching horizons through theme-based VR showrooms along with the unique feature of collaboration and relationship building – all aiming towards elevating brands in the digital world and enhancing customer loyalty by giving them an inclusive and creative shopping experience. Innovators : Rupal Sethi, Sanjeev V. Narsipur, Dhruvil Bavishi, Saikiran Kolluri and Abhishek Sappandi Data Command Center Description:Bad Data Quality &amp; In-effective Data Management for an organization increases IT costs, reduces workforce efficiency and may lead to lost opportunities. Solution is to create a Virtual Data Command Center by combining the power of Artificial Intelligence and 3D Data Visualization to bring a paradigm shift in the way data is currently managed within organizations. This helps: 1) Explore Data &amp; Metadata 2) Perform Data Operations 3) Create a self-serviceable Data Market Place Effectively Managing Data can lead to average cost savings of 33%, while boosting revenue by an average of 31%. Consolidation of systems can save up to 25% of IT Costs Innovators : Prashant Wason, Amit Malhotra, Saikat Jana, Sagar Sanjeev and Ashutosh Pandey Can’t wait for the big reveal on our supreme GTIC 2020 winner? Stay tuned for the verdict. We wish all the teams the best of luck.","post_excerpt":"","post_content":"<style>*{marg