s, the moment you’ve all been waiting for is finally here, ATCI! We’ve got the names of the Global Technology Innovation Contest (GTIC) 2020 – India finalists. Let’s tip our hats to the incredible tech innovators and give them a big round of applause!\r\n\r\nThese 14 teams chosen from the 86 prototypes—truly exemplify our zeal to think outside the box and innovate, both for business and society.\r\n\r\nWithout further ado, let’s find out who they are. What’s more? You can take the jury’s seat and vote for your favorite innovation to help them win the People’s Choice Award!\r\n\r\n<strong style=\"font-weight: 600;\">Got a personal favorite?</strong>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 25px;\"><a class=\"link\" href=\"https://quicksurvey.accenture.com/98ceb862-355a-4151-bbf2-02bdac86f70d/questions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://in.accenture.com/india/wp-content/uploads/sites/548/2019/07/vote-white.png\" alt=\"\" />Vote for your favorite GTIC Team or Idea: People’s Choice Award</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Theme: Innovate for Society</h3>\r\n<div class=\"grayBox\">\r\n<h4>Intelligent Pandemic Management Using Game Theory</h4>\r\n<div class=\"slideTxt\">\r\n<div class=\"borderLine\"><b>Problem Statement:</b> <strong>“Every Battle is Won or Lost Before it is Ever Fought”</strong> This is the famous advice from Sun Tzu’s Art of War. The situation we are in today is no less than a war with an invisible enemy – COVID Virus. Today, the governments are struggling to manage pandemics as they do no have an efficient mechanism to strategize with limited resources and control the pandemic.</div>\r\n<div class=\"borderLine\"><b>Solution:</b> We bring <strong>‘Chanakya – An intelligent pandemic management system’</strong> based on <strong>Game theory</strong> that anticipates the next step of the enemy and proposes next best action. Here, the infected patients are the attackers and healthcare, police and other essential support staff as defenders. Our strategy engine built using <strong>Stackelberg Game Algorithm</strong> determines the next best action based on the moves of the attacker and the payoff. Using <strong>machine learning</strong>, the game learns from past strategies and outcomes to devise new strategies.</div>\r\n<div class=\"borderLine\"><b>Benefit:</b> Decision makers can now simulate strategies with <strong>Chanakya</strong> at their fingertips to make smart and quick decisions. With our system in place, we all will be better prepared for our next pandemic and save millions of lives and their livelihood.</div>\r\n<div class=\"borderLine noBorder\"><b>Innovators :</b> Roshan Clive Dmello, Sweta Mahendrakar, Ashwija Shetty, Shraddha Modi and Shweta Bhanushali</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div class=\"grayBox\">\r\n<h4>Posture Corrector using Deep Learning Framework</h4>\r\n<div class=\"slideTxt\">\r\n<div class=\"borderLine\"><b>Description:</b> Ergonomics, Stress and Long Sitting (ESL) lead to poor posture and for every 60min of slouch you reduce life expectancy by 22min.\r\nSolutions for posture corrector exist but not popular as they focus on generating alerts but not on the holistic idea of managing the ESL effect through activism. This is where our cloud AI/ML based solution, “WellErt” creates a differentiation\r\n“WellErt” uses the device camera and with user consent monitors the the slouch using AI without compromising data privacy. Based on user readings the cloud ML model generates curated alerts/activities to engage the user into a cycle of activism and making upright posture a good habit</div>\r\n<div class=\"borderLine noBorder\"><b>Innovators :</b> Lavanya Sripathi, Shailesh Chaphekar, Ajay Merulingkar, Ashish Saraswat and Kalyani Jadhav</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"grayBox\">\r\n<h4>Unleashing the Potential of Digital Personas</h4>\r\n<div class=\"slideTxt\">\r\n<div class=\"borderLine\"><b>Situation:</b> We need STEAM not STEM to prepare kids for 4th Industrial revolution. 13%