 are sexual in nature, such as any advances or requests; any verbal, written, or social media interactions; any physical touching or physical behaviour. Some Do’s and Don’ts Keep calm, always communicate thoughtfully and professionally. Practice respectful behaviour. Avoid inappropriate jokes. Dress appropriately for video calls and maintain a professional posture. Make sure your background is work appropriate. Do not insist on video calls if a colleague is uncomfortable. Refrain from discussing appearance or attire of a colleague, (even as a compliment). Always check if it is a comfortable time to connect for a call, especially if it is outside of working hours Refrain from sending / taking or displaying sexually suggestive, lewd and/or indecent pictures or other materials. Avoid unwanted attention, such as phone calls, texts or messages to an individual without a work-related reason for the contact. Avoid unwanted physical contact of a sexual nature. Do not use your position of power to make unwanted sexual advances or imply that employment decisions may be affected by acceptance or rejection of sexual advances. Avoid discussing and probing for personal details. Be aware of any unconscious bias that you may have. REMEMBER: It’s never the intent but always about the impact. So always, keep calm and communicate thoughtfully and professionally. Practice respectful behavior at all times. SPEAK UP! Accenture has zero tolerance for all forms of sexually inappropriate behavior. Please bookmark these helpline details and report any concerns to your HR representative immediately: Write in to POSH.India@accenture.com Contact the Accenture Business Ethics Helpline To know more on POSH: Read the Prevention of Sexual Harassment – POSH (Policy 1005) Complete the Prevention of Sexual Harassment at the Workplace training To know more on Conduct Counts, visit: Code of Business Ethics page The Conduct Counts page Here’s to a safe, respectful and harassment free work environment – a