a"},{"aggregator_short_tag":"Location","aggmeta_short_tag":"Location","aggregator_siteid":"169","aggregatorunreadcount":"77","sitegrouporder":"2","sortid":"11","short_tag":"India","article_id":"2423009","post_title":"Success story: Hello, faster telco. DevOps Dojo here!","post_content_stripped":"The client is the world's largest telecommunications company and North America’s leading provider of mobile and fixed telephone services. They offer voice, video, data and Internet telecommunications and professional services to businesses, consumers and government agencies. Challenge The client wanted to speed up time-to-market with a digital platform that helps retail, online sales, and services channels deliver effortless digital interactions. The client also needed a skilled and experienced team to manage the platform. Solution Accenture took over in enhancing and managing the client’s digital platform to streamline sales and services delivery. The platform employs modern eCommerce architecture required for web-scale operations and powered by microservices. We formed a shared team to manage the platform and provide DevOps as-a-service to multiple development teams. The shared team is responsible for building and developing environments, providing access, and ensuring these environments are always up and running. The team also deploys more than 200 microservices in a week across various production and non-production compute platforms. These services cover multistage pipelines—including building, testing and deploying new additions to the platform as well as running security tests. Plus, they take charge in troubleshooting and supporting various real-time issues related to application and infrastructure. Then, we launched the DevOps Dojo Model to train and upskill the team in handling various digital and automation tools such as Kubernetes, Docker and Kafka. We conducted short iteration-based learning cycles and hands-on activities across 12 hyper sprints, with 2.5 days per sprint, covering five squads with 30 participants in six weeks. With these sessions, we enhanced the technical agility and capability of the team to manage the client’s platform at speed and scale. Results By enhancing the digital platform and implementing our DevOps Dojo initiative, we helped: Improve overall productivity by 35 percent for the client. Reduce microservices deployment time by 33 percent. Cut resolution time for Kubernetes issues by 37 percent. Decrease analysis time for Kubernetes alerts by 50 percent. Key contacts To know how our digital platform enhancements and DevOps Dojo program accelerate time-to-market for the client, contact Ravi Shankar Nori, Vijeth Hegde,  or K.S. Prasanna Kumar.","post_excerpt":"","post_content":"The client is the world's largest telecommunications company and North America’s leading provider of mobile and fixed telephone services. They offer voice, video, data and Internet telecommunications and professional services to businesses, consumers and government agencies.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #00ff00; font-size: 14pt;\">Challenge</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThe client wanted to speed up time-to-market with a digital platform that helps retail, online sales, and services channels deliver effortless digital interactions. The client also needed a skilled and experienced team to manage the platform.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #00ff00; font-size: 14pt;\">Solution</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAccenture took over in enhancing and managing the client’s digital platform to streamline sales and services delivery. The platform employs modern eCommerce architecture required for web-scale operations and powered by microservices.\r\n\r\nWe formed a shared team to manage the platform and provide DevOps as-a-service to multiple development teams. The shared team is responsible for building and developing environments, providing access, and ensuring these environments are always up and running. The team also deploys more than 200 microservices in a week across various production and non-production compute platforms. These services cover multistage pipelines—including building, testing and deploying new additions to the platform as well as running security tests. Plus, they take charge in troubleshooting and supporting various real-time issues related to application and infrastructure.\r\n\r\nThen, we launched the <a href=\"https://circles.accenture.com/fb4f24ee-2bbf-4e97-90f0-ea735f013ac6?tab=discussions\">DevOps Dojo Model</a> to train and upskill the team in handling various digital and automation tools such as Kubernetes, Docker and Kafka. We conducted short iteration-based learning cycles and hands-on activities across 12 hyper sprints, with 2.5 days per sprint, covering five squads with 30 participants in six weeks. With these sessions, we enhanced the technical agility and capability of the team to manage the client’s platform at speed and scale.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-56034\" src=\"https://in.accenture.com/india/wp-content/uploads/sites/548/2020/09/Alin-think.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"620\" height=\"381\" />\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #00ff00; font-size: 14pt;\">Results</span></strong>\r\n\r\nBy enhancing the digital platform and implementing our DevOps Dojo initiative, we helped:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Improve overall productivity by 35 percent for the client.</li>\r\n \t<li>Reduce microservices deployment time by 33 percent.</li>\r\n \t<li>Cut resolution time for Kubernetes issues by 37 percent.</li>\r\n \t<li>Decrease analysis time for Kubernetes alerts by 50 percent.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #00ff00; font-size: 14pt;\">Key contacts</span></strong>\r\n\r\nTo know how our digital platform enhancements and DevOps Dojo program accelerate time-to-market for the client, contact <a href=\"https://people.accenture.com/People/user/ravi.shankar.nori\">Ravi Shankar Nori</a>, <a href=\"https://people.accenture.com/People/user/vijeth.s.hegde\">Vijeth Hegde</a>,  or <a href=\"https://people.accenture.com/People/user/k.s.prasanna.kumar\">K.S. Prasanna Kumar</a>.","post_link":"https://in.accenture.com/india/?site=1&blog=548&p=56029","site_url":"https://in.accenture.com/india/","post_thumb":"https://cdn.in.accenture.com/prod/wp-content/uploads/sites/548/2020/09/28154042/11629_jpg.jpg","post_date":"2020-09-30 11:02:53","post_modified":"2020-09-30 20:42:08","isread":"0","article_score":"0.000000","isfeatured":"0","source_short_tag":"India","category_url":"https://in.accenture.com/india/","source_url":"https://in.accenture.com/india"},{"aggregator_short_tag":"Location","aggmeta_short_tag":"Location","aggregator_siteid":"169","aggregatorunreadcount":"77","sitegrouporder":"2","sortid":"12","short_tag":"India","article_id":"2433991","post_title":"Success story: Abraka-BAMA: Faster farm-to-market with automation","post_content_stripped":"The client BAMA Gruppen is Norway’s largest wholesaler of fruits and vegetables. The company has five divisions: Retail, HORECA supplies, Industry (processed food), Service Trade (convenience stores) and Flowers. Challenge The client faced the following challenges: Poor customer experience The client encountered high turnaround time for the distribution of fruits, vegetables and flowers due to manual system testing, which also led to unreliable and error-prone business critical applications. Delayed time-to-market Manual deployment processes increased risks for potential delays in inbound operations such as procurement, cross docking and shipment of fruits and vegetables from supplier to client warehouse. Outbound operations also faced delays due to error-prone activities for shipping goods from the warehouse to consumers. Lack of ticket insights The client needed an analytic reporting tool to diagnose recurring issues and predict future inflow of incidents. Manual creation of essential dashboards also made monthly service reporting a cumbersome task. Solution Accenture has been providing application maintenance support for the client through the Microsoft Dynamics AX2012 ERP solution, including WAX for advanced warehouse management and TRAX for transportation management modules. To help the client address operational challenges, we used our automation and data science expertise to: Develop automated scripts using Avanade Software and Cloud Services (SCS) automation framework built with Coded UI for performing smoke testing. For executing scripts, we can either use Microsoft Test management (MTM) or BAT (batch) files using Task scheduler. These scripts run every day across three pre-production environments. The client achieved 99 percent automation through scheduled jobs. Create an automated build and deployment solution using PowerShell, which is configured as a task-in-task scheduler without dependency on the Release Manager. It helped accelerate the shipment process. The PowerShell scripts, assisted by Azure scheduler, also helped achieve 98 percent automation. Leverage myWizard Virtual Data Scientist (VDS) tool for effective analysis of incidents and problem reports. Real-time graphs in VDS provide accurate status of incident reporting. The tool’s graph export feature has also eased the dashboard preparation. Results With our automation and myWizard VDS solution, we helped the client: Reduce efforts in deployment processes by approximately 52 percent using custom automation scripts and save approximately US$5,120. Lessen dependency on Release Manager by approximately 98 percent using our automated deployment solution. As such, we eliminated the business risks associated with product deployment. Improve insights and enhance stakeholder reporting using the VDS tool, leading to 33 percent saved effort and translating to US$170.6 in cost savings. Achieve approximately US$11K and 500 hours overall savings in FY20. Testimonials “This is very good. I appreciate the focus on automation that you and the team have!” —Andreas Kvernland-Berg, Program Manager, Bama IT Key contacts To know how we helped BAMA Grupper improve operations with automation, contact Borger Mobraten, Girish Aswathanarayana, Rohit R. Sharma, Rohit N. Sharma, Ashish Panth or Dipti Matpati.","post_excerpt":"","post_content":"The client BAMA Gruppen is Norway’s largest wholesaler of fruits and vegetables. The company has five divisions: Retail, HORECA supplies, Industry (processed food), Service Trade (convenience stores) and Flowers.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #00ff00; font-size: 14pt;\">Challenge</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThe client faced the following challenges:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li><strong>Poor customer experience</strong>\r\nThe client encountered high turnaround time for the distribution of fruits, vegetables and flowers due to manual system testing, which also led to unreliable and error-prone business critical applications.</li>\r\n \t<li><strong>Delayed time-to-market</strong>\r\nManual deployment processes increased risks for potential delays in inbound operations such as procurement, cross docking and shipment of fruits and vegetables from supplier to client warehouse. Outbound operations also faced delays due to error-prone activities for shipping goods from the warehouse to consumers.</li>\r\n \t<li><strong>Lack of ticket insights</strong>\r\nThe client needed an analytic reporting tool to diagnose recurring issues and predict future inflow of incidents. Manual creation of essential dashboards also made monthly service reporting a cumbersome task.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #00ff00; font-size: 14pt;\">Solution</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAccenture has been providing application maintenance support for the client through the Microsoft Dynamics AX2012 ERP solution, including WAX for advanced warehouse management and TRAX for transportation management modules. To help the client address operational challenges, we used our automation and data science expertise to:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Develop automated scripts using Ava