ing to a joint research report by Accenture and Girls Who Code. The research, “Resetting Tech Culture,” identifies three key factors for an inclusive culture and five cultural practices which could help retain 1.4 million young women in technology roles by 2030. Find more in this press release. INNOVATION Giving designers the edge with Tech Due to rapid changes in the field of product design, designers, manufacturers and engineers are experiencing new challenges, including growing demand for customization, agility and minimized waste approach. In the latest Tech Innovation Insider feature, we share how our Labbers, Alpana Dubey and Nick Akiona, are pushing the boundaries of advanced technologies to enable the future of design using immersive experiences, intelligent tools and collaboration capabilities. CLOUD FIRST Sustainability potential of cloud Sustainable cloud positions companies to deliver on new commitments: carbon reduction and responsible innovation. A focused approach on cloud migration can reduce global CO2 emissions by 59 million tons, drive greater circularity and result in more sustainable products and services. Learn more from the new report, “The green behind the cloud.” MAAG It’s a wrap at ASPARA Accenture put on a great show at APSARA, Alibaba’s annual flagship event, on September 17-18. Julie Sweet was invited to speak at the keynote session and made her debut Chinese public speech, which was extremely well received. During the event, we also announced the Accenture-Alibaba Joint Cloud Migration and Transformation CoE. Find out more about the event and watch session replays. INCLUSION &amp; DIVERSITY Thrive with Arianna Huffington &amp; Ellyn Shook Join us on October 6 at 10:30 AM EST or 10:00 PM EST for Why Mental Resiliency Matters – and How to Build It - a conversation with Arianna Huffington, Thrive Global Founder &amp; CEO and Ellyn Shook, Accenture’s Chief Leadership and Human Resources Officer. Participants will learn how Accenture and Thr