ture of product design. Due to rapid changes happening in this area, designers, manufacturers and engineers are experiencing new challenges that include growing demand for customization, agility and minimized waste approach. Alpana and Nick show us how technology and AI-enabled digital tools can offer solutions and opportunities in this space. Even though design was traditionally driven by human experience and creativity, it turns out that tech advancements can play a significant role in this process, too. Read the blog to find out more about immersive experiences, intelligent tools and new levels of collaboration enabled by applying AI,  natural language processing, knowledge graph-driven techniques, augmented and virtual reality in fashion and automotive industries. More About Technology Innovation: As part of the global Accenture Technology organization, Technology Innovation was formed to make it simpler to “drive continuous innovation and agility at massive scale”—one of our five key priorities in Accenture’s Next Generation Growth Model (NGGM). Previously, we had pockets of innovation operating independently in Technology. Now we have combined all the necessary components: Accenture Labs, Accenture Ventures, Accenture Liquid Studios, and our newly created Technology Incubation Group—Multi-party systems/Blockchain, Extended Reality and Quantum Computing—into one practice. This makes it faster and easier than ever before for clients to access Accenture’s technology innovation capabilities! Why is this important? Because innovation has become a C-level priority. It is ingrained in our clients’ business and technology strategies. Our team is ready to collaborate with you and help you package world-class innovation into solutions for your clients! Now for a look at some of the exciting opportunities we are already delivering… Three Accenture XR projects named as VR Award Finalists -The Academy of International Extended Reality named three Accenture XR projects as VR Award Finalists. The VR Awards annual program celebrates outstanding achievements in VR. Applying neuromorphic computing to help wheelchair-bound pediatric patients -  Accenture and Intel are supporting a neuromorphic computing research project led by the Neuro-Biomorphic Engineering Lab (NBEL) at the Open University of Israel in collaboration with ALYN Hospital, Israel’s leading pediatric and adolescent rehabilitation center. Funded by Accenture through its participation in the Intel Neuromorphic Research Community (INRC), the project is focused on developing and testing a wheelchair-mounted robotic arm to assist patients with performing daily tasks. Read more about the impact of this research in the news release. Accenture Immersive Collaboration Platform – Our new internal extended reality framework to create multi-user, photorealistic virtual environments for remote collaboration, training, workshops and digital events for our clients. Watch our video to learn more – the possibilities for implementation are practically endless! Digital Dollar LIVE Webinar – As our world is becoming digitally native, the functionality of money must evolve accordingly. Accenture, in collaboration with the Digital Dollar Foundation, is leading the conversation on US Central Bank Digital Currencies (CBDC) with the Digital Dollar Project (DDP) and our joint whitepaper. Watch the  Digital Dollar LIVE webinar replay to hear from leaders in this space explore the Digital Dollar and understand what’s next. Accenture Ventures Targets Innovative Edge Computing Technology with Investment in Synadia Communications – To help bring edge computing capabilities to our clients, Accenture Ventures has made a strategic minority investment in Synadia Communications, the company behind the production-proven open source NATS.io project.&lt; Security Technology Vision – New Accenture research identifies an elite set of global enterprises—what we call the “alpha innovators”—and the collaborative actions they are taking to achieve continuous innovation securely! Technology Vision Digital Health report – Digital healthcare experiences are more important than ever for helping consumers feel engaged, important and informed. One of our latest reports, Accenture Digital Health Technology Vision 2020, focuses on how healthcare organizations are using technologies like AI and robotics in their new, innovative experiences. Read the news release and check out the full report. Technology Vision COVID-19 report – The COVID-19 pandemic has not slowed innovation; it has amplified it to historic levels. Considering the ongoing challenges, we revisited our Technology Vision 2020 trends to explore how companies can go about Driving Value and Values during COVID-19. Read the article and learn more about how to share the information with your clients. I’ll be back in two weeks with more Technology Innovation solutions!","post_excerpt":"Read the next edition of Tech Innovation Insider and find out how Accenture Labs is offering solutions to the growing demand for customization, agility and minimized waste approach that designers, manufacturers and engineers are seeking in the area of product design.","post_content":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe id=\"kmsembed-1_mpt8d26y\" class=\"kmsembed\" title=\"Kaltura Player\" src=\"https://mediaexchange.accenture.com/embed/secure/iframe/entryId/1_mpt8d26y/uiConfId/27188232\" width=\"608\" height=\"456\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\nWelcome back to our next edition of <span style=\"color: #7500c0;\"><strong>Tech Innovation Insider</strong></span>, the Technology Innovation bi-weekly communication! We feature the best of Technology Innovation including client stories, solutions, assets and prototypes that we are delivering to our clients, Accenture and society.\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #7500c0;\"><strong>Featured story:</strong></span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-25369 aligncen