er to create a self-consistent, interoperable and representative infrastructure model of a \"micro\" green supply chain for e-mobility.\r\n\r\nWe're developing a platform in where stakeholders, including biomass producers, send the raw materials that will be produced in biomethane to the production plants. Through the platform, GSE will receive the information of interest in real time, issuing the incentives.\r\n\r\nFor E-Mobility, the users search on their own Mobile App the recharging stations powered by «Green Energy», recharge their vehicle, and receive tokens on the basis of the quantity of energy coming from sustainable sources used for recharging. Tokens can also be used to purchase services supplied by partners/CPO who joined the platform.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"alberto.n.bonadonna@accenture.com\">More info</a></span>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<table style=\"width: 815px; border-collapse: collapse;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 237px; text-align: left; vertical-align: top;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-25335\" src=\"https://in.accenture.com/accenturetechnology/wp-content/uploads/sites/46/2020/09/IES09292020-044-300x233.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"233\" /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 572px; text-align: left; vertical-align: top;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>VR Enterprise Solution of the Year: <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #851cdd;\"><a style=\"color: #851cdd; text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"https://in.accenture.com/labs/?site=1&amp;blog=369&amp;p=3215&amp;preview=true\">Accenture Immersive Collaboration Platform (ICP)</a></span></span></strong></span>\r\nOur internal extended reality platform creates multi-user, photorealistic virtual environments for remote collaboration, training, workshops and digital events for our clients.\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: #851cdd;\"><a style=\"color: #851cdd; text-decoration: un