 United Kingdom &amp; Ireland (UKI) market unit, has decided to retire at the end of FY21. I am delighted to announce that Simon Eaves, who has been serving as our Chief Strategy Officer, will succeed Olly in leading our UKI market unit on January 1, 2021—which will allow for a smooth transition in our third largest market unit globally. Simon will continue as a member of our Global Management Committee. Olly will continue as Chairman of the UKI until the end of FY21. I also am delighted to announce that Bhaskar Ghosh, who currently serves as Advisor to the CEO, will become our Chief Strategy Officer, effective immediately, as Simon begins his transition back to the UK from his current residence in Atlanta. Olly has been a force in our business and a role model for how to develop deep leadership skills and experience. He has held global, market, industry and client account leadership roles—and in all roles has been very focused on caring for our people and serving clients. As head of UKI for nearly ten years, Olly has not only successfully led the overall business but has been deeply and personally engaged in serving our clients on their most critical transformation journeys. Earlier in his career, Olly was Chief Operating Officer for our Management Consulting and Products groups. Olly was a key contributor to developing our Next Generation Growth Model and our new purpose (which we will announce in a few weeks). He has been an important part of our Global Management Committee. Olly models his strong commitment to the community in his roles as a founding trustee and chairman of Movement to Work. He is on the board of the UK government's Inclusive Economy Partnership and an advisory board member of the Productivity Leadership Group and Innovate UK. He also sits on the Professional &amp; Business Services Council and the UK's Digital Economy Council and is a member of the Made Smarter Commission. In his role as Chairman of UKI, Olly will act as an advisor to Simon and will focus primarily on our work with our clients and client teams to pursue major, market-making transformational deals. He will also represent Accenture with key external groups. On a personal note, I want to recognize Olly’s role in my development as a leader. When I became the CEO of North America in 2015 and transitioned from being General Counsel to lead a major business unit, I asked Olly for help. Over the years, he has generously shared his advice, expertise and time with me, acting as an important sounding board. Even more important, he was inspiring to me as a leader who solved for our people, clients and Accenture; who cared deeply for his work; and who makes a difference. And since I became CEO, I have enjoyed working side-by-side with Olly at clients, including Barclays and British Telecom. I could not be happier for Olly and his family for his well-deserved retirement, but I am very glad that he will be here for FY21, continuing to make a tremendous impact at this important time. Simon brings a broad range of experience—from global, to market, sales to industry and strategy, and a track record of building deep client relationships and creating value. He also lives our Leadership Essentials in all respects. Over the last six months, in his role as Chief Strategy Officer, Simon has helped lead the rapid evolution of our industry points of view related to COVID-19 in our Now Next industry campaign. He also co-led, with corporate development, the evolution of our global Ventures &amp; Acquisitions strategy for the future, working with our Market CEOs and Growth &amp; Strategy team. He continued to work at clients, including Walgreens, AICPA, Coke, ABI and Mars. Prior to his current role, Simon was our Group Chief Executive of Products and played a pivotal role in the migration to the Next Generation Growth Model. Simon has been our Global Sales Lead of Products and Growth &amp; Strategy Lead of Products, holding these positions for several years. Simon also led our Products Customer &amp; Channel Consulting practice. He has significant experience from the UKI where he was previously Client Service Group lead for Products UKI and among many client account lead roles has been Diamond Client Account Lead for Unilever, SABMiller and Argos. Simon has lived in Atlanta since 2017, in addition to working globally in many markets around the world over the course of his career, which is essential to our strategy of bringing global to local, and local to global. He is an active participant in Accenture’s Skills to Succeed efforts and an advocate for inclusion and diversity, including being a passionate supporter of our LGBTQ Ally program. I know he is very excited to return to the UKI and take on this new role. Over the last several months, Bhaskar has been the team captain, on behalf of the Global Management Committee, of the creation of our Strategy 2025, which we will share more about in a couple of weeks when we announce our new purpose and brand. In addition, as advisor to the CEO since March 1, Bhaskar has focused on leading our Industry X growth strategy, working with Nigel Stacey and his multi-service leadership team. Prior to his current role, during the last six years, Bhaskar was the group chief executive of Accenture Technology Services. Bhaskar was critical to helping shape and implement our Rotation to the New strategy. He had overall responsibility for our Technology business, directing strategy and investments, and leading platforms, products and global technology delivery—working closely with our Strategy, Consulting, Digital, and Security groups. Under Bhaskar’s leadership, Accenture Technology Services made outstanding progress, rapidly rotating to the New and enabling clients to lead in the New. More than 200,000 Accenture Technology people were trained around the world in New IT. Accenture also strengthened New IT offerings around data, cloud and security. At the same time, Accenture opened a groundbreaking Innovation Hub in Bengaluru with a focus on driving innovation at scale, and a network of more than 18 Liquid Studios around the world. Bhaskar has personally provided leadership to developing cutting-edge technology solutions, including: the technology automation platform myWizard; Accenture’s cloud assessment and migration platform, MyNav; and the value-led ERP implementation platform of Accenture myConcerto. As an innovator, Bhaskar has been awarded six patents in the area of software engineering and platform development. Bhaskar also is passionate about inclusion and diversity, helping lead many innovative changes, which, among other things, have helped Technology—our largest Services area—be instrumental to our current achievement of 45 percent women at Accenture. As Chief Strategy Officer, Bhaskar will be responsible for our strategy, including our investment strategy and ensuring execution of our strategy across Accenture, working with his colleagues on the Global Management Committee. He also will have management oversight for the development of all assets and offerings across Services to ensure more consistent integrated assets and multi-services offerings in the future, which is core to our new strategy. In addition, he will be responsible for Accenture Research and our Responsible Business team. He will also continue his role leading our Industry X growth strategy. Please join me in thanking and recognizing Olly for his ongoing exceptional leadership, and in congratulating Simon and Bhaskar on their new roles. I look forward to celebrating Olly and thanking him again at the end of the fiscal year! Best Regards,","post_excerpt":"I am writing to announce three leadership changes on our Global Management Committee. ","post_content":"I am writing to announce three leadership changes on our Global Management Committee.\r\n\r\nAfter 28 years of service and an incredible career, <a href=\"https://people.accenture.com/People/user/oliver.benzecry\"><strong>Olly Benzecry</strong></a>, who leads our United Kingdom &amp; Ireland (UKI) market unit, has decided to retire at the end of FY21. I am delighted to announce that <a href=\"https://people.accenture.com/People/user/simon.eaves\"><strong>Simon Eaves</strong></a>, who has been serving as our Chief Strategy Officer, will succeed Olly in leading our UKI market unit on January 1, 2021—which will allow for a smooth transition in our third largest market unit globally. Simon will continue as a member of our Global Management Committee. Olly will continue as Chairman of the UKI until the end of FY21. I also am delighted to announce that <a href=\"https://people.accenture.com/People/user/bhaskar.ghosh\"><strong>Bhaskar Ghosh</strong></a>, who currently serves as Advisor to the CEO, will become our Chief Strategy Officer, effective immediately, as Simon begins his transition back to the UK from his current residence in Atlanta.\r\n\r\n<strong><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3696 alignright\" src=\"https://in.accenture.com/ceo/wp-content/uploads/sites/604/2020/10/olly-300x226.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"226\" />Olly</strong> has been a force in our business and a role model for how to develop deep leadership skills and experience. He has held global, market, industry and client account leadership roles—and in all roles has been very focused on caring for our people and serving clients. As head of UKI for nearly ten years, Olly has not only successfully led the overall business but has been deeply and personally engaged in serving our clients on their most critical transformation journeys. Earlier in his career, Olly was Chief Operating Officer for our Management Consulting and Products groups. Olly was a key contributor to developing our Next Generation Growth Model and our new purpose (which we will announce in a few weeks). He has been an important part of our Global Management Committee.\r\n\r\nOlly models his strong commitment to the community in his roles as a founding trustee and chairman of Movement to Work. He is on the board of the UK government's Inclusive Economy Partnership and an advisory board member of the Productivity Leadership Group and Innovate UK. He also sits on the Professional &amp; Business Services Council and the UK's Digital Economy Council and is a member of the Made Smarter Commission.\r\n\r\nIn his role as Chairman of UKI, Olly will act as an advisor to Simon and will focus primarily on our work with our clients and client teams to pursue major, market-making transformational deals. He will also represent Accenture with key external groups.\r\n\r\nOn a personal note, I want to recognize Olly’s role in my development as a leader. When I became the CEO of North America in 2015 and transitioned from being General Counsel to lead a major business unit, I asked Olly for help. Over the years, he has generously shared his advice, expertise and time with me, acting as an important sounding board. Even more important, he was inspiring to me as a leader who solved for our people, clients and Accenture; who cared deeply for his work; and who makes a difference. And since I became CEO, I have enjoyed working side-by-side with Olly at clients, including Barclays and British Telecom. I could not be happier for Olly and his family for his well-deserved retirement, but I am very glad that he will be here for FY21, continuing to make a tremendous impact at this important time.\r\n\r\n<strong><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3697 alignright\" src=\"https://in.accenture.com/ceo/wp-content/uploads/sites/604/2020/10/simon.eaves_-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />Simon</strong> brings a broad range of experience—from global, to market, sales to industry and strategy, and a track record of building deep client relationships and creating value. He also lives our <a href=\"https://ts.accenture.com/sites/InternalCommunicationsCenter/Communication%20Attachments/Leadership%20Essentials_FY21.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Leadership Essentials</a> in all respects. Over the last six months, in his role as Chief Strategy Officer, Simon has helped lead the rapid evolution of our industry points of view related to COVID-19 in our Now Next industry campaign. He also co-led, with corporate development, the evolution of our global Ventures &amp; Acquisitions strategy for the future, working with our Market CEOs and Growth &amp; Strategy team. He continued to work at clients, including Walgreens, AICPA, Coke, ABI and Mars.\r\n\r\nPrior to his current role, Simon was our Group Chief Executive of Products and played a pivotal role in the migration to the Next Generation Growth Model. Simon has been our Global Sales Lead of Products and Growth &amp; Strategy Lead of Products, holding these positions for several years. Simon also led our Products Customer &amp; Channel Consulting practice. He has significant experience from the UKI where he was previously Client Service Group lead for Products UKI and among many client account lead roles has been Diamond Client Account Lead for Unilever, SABMiller and Argos. Simon has lived in Atlanta since 2017, in addition to working globally in many markets around the world over the course of his career, which is essential to our strategy of bringing global to local, and local to global. He is an active participant in Accenture’s Skills to Succeed efforts and an advocate for inclusion and diversity, including being a passionate supporter of our LGBTQ Ally program. I know he is very excited to return to the UKI and take on this new role.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3695 alignright\" src=\"https://in.accenture.com/ceo/wp-content/uploads/sites/604/2020/10/Bghosh-300x287.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"287\" />Over the last several months, <strong>Bhaskar </strong>has been the team captain, on behalf of the Global Management Committee, of the creation of our Strategy 2025, which we will share more about in a couple of weeks when we announce our new purpose and brand. In addition, as advisor to the CEO since March 1, Bhaskar has focused on leading our Industry X growth strategy, working with <a href=\"https://people.accenture.com/People/user/nigel.j.stacey\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Nigel Stacey</strong></a> and his multi-service leadership team.\r\n\r\nPrior to his current role, during the last six years, Bhaskar was the group chief executive of Accenture Technology Services. Bhaskar was critical to helping shape and implement our Rotation to the New strategy. He had overall responsibility for our Technology business, directing strategy and investments, and leading platforms, products and global technology delivery—working closely with our Strategy, Consulting, Digital, and Security groups.\r\n\r\nUnder Bhaskar’s leadership, Accenture Technology Services made outstanding progress, rapidly rotating to the New and enabling clients to lead in the New. More than 200,000 Accenture Technology people were trained around the world in New IT. Accenture also strengthened New IT offerings around data, cloud and security. At the same time, Accenture opened a groundbreaking Innovation Hub in Bengaluru with a focus on driving innovation at scale, and a network of more than 18 Liquid Studios around the world.\r\n\r\nBhaskar has personally provided leadership to developing cutting-edge technology solutions, including: the technology automation platform myWizard; Accenture’s cloud assessment and migration platform, MyNav; and the value-led ERP implementation platform of Accenture myConcerto. As an innovator, Bhaskar has been awarded six patents in the area of software engineering and platform development.\r\n\r\nBhaskar also is passionate about inclusion and diversity, helping lead many innovative changes, which, among other things, have helped Technology—our largest Services area—be instrumental to our current achievement of 45