tegrouporder":"4","sortid":"24","short_tag":"Julie Here","article_id":"2436846","post_title":"Making the impossible possible with SDG Ambition","post_content_stripped":"Watch the conversation Julie is featured at 29:25 on Accenture's commitment; 39:48 on supply chain transformation and 44:15 with advice for leaders.  As part of the historic 75th session of the UN General Assembly, CEO Julie Sweet was a featured speaker on the UN’s Uniting Business LIVE, a virtual forum of leaders from business, government and civil society convening to discuss and drive business ambition on the United Nations’ 17 Sustainable Development Goals, which cover issues such as inequality, poverty, education and climate—into their core business. Julie joined SAP CEO Christian Klein and 3M CEO Mike Roman for a conversation moderated by Executive Director and CEO of the UN Global Compact Sanda Ojiambo about moving beyond incremental progress to transformation through SDG Ambition , our joint partnership with SAP and UN Global Compact, and most recently, 3M as Patron Sponsor, to challenge and support companies in integrating the 17 Sustainable Development Goals, which cover issues such as inequality, poverty, education and climate—into their core business. In introducing the session, Ojiambo noted that “the business of business is truly no longer just business,” especially today. “The next few months provide a window of opportunity for all of us to make the seemingly impossible, possible. It's a time for reinvention, a time to reset, and a time for rebuilding to shape a sustainable future,’ she said. “For the private sector, this reinvention must address the wider societal and environmental impacts of business strategy in ways that drive both business benefit and societal transformation.” Julie expanded on the point, underscoring the role of technology. “If we think about it in the context of COVID, we need to accelerate digital because we are now in a remote, contactless world,” Julie said. “This is a once in a lifetime opportunity to re-platform global business through technology and change the business of business by building sustainability into the design.” To do so, and to further accelerate business action in achieving the SDGs, the SDG Ambition program launched new guidance to provide business leaders with directional support on measuring and managing sustainability performance. Ambition Guide: Setting Goals for the Decade of Action establishes the initial set of SDG Ambition Benchmarks that challenge organizations to set more ambitious goals and targets in the areas in which business is positioned to have a substantial impact. Integration Guide: Designing Business Systems for the SDGs presents the approach through which the 10 SDG Ambition Benchmarks can be integrated into core business processes and systems to enable effective measurement and management of sustainability performance. SDG Ambition Benchmark Reference Sheets provide illustrative details regarding the steps to integrate each of these benchmarks into a company’s business systems, as well as the key design decision required to engage technology partners. Collaborating with speed and humility Julie also shared how SDG Ambition underscores the humility and speed required when it comes to organizations working together. “To me, these collaborations demonstrate that we have to be humble and we have to learn from others,” she said. “Companies, governments and NGOs all have different perspectives and are doing great things, so having the humility to say we need to come together and learn from each other will give us the speed that is so critical to creating a better future.” What’s Next &amp; Learn More Through the UN Global Compact and their Local Network teams, Accenture will be supporting the SDG Ambition Accelerator kicking off in January 2021. This program will guide 1,000+ companies, including many of our clients, in raising their sustainability ambitions and more deeply integrating the SDGs.  To learn more about the Accelerator, visit the SDG Ambition website. To discuss applying SDG Ambition with your clients, please contact Michael D. Hughes.","post_excerpt":"As part of the historic 75th session of the UN General Assembly, CEO Julie Sweet was a featured speaker on the UN’s Uniting Business LIVE, a virtual forum of leaders from business, government and civil society convening to discuss and drive business ambition on the United Nations’ 17 Sustainable Development Goals,","post_content":"<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong><a href=\"https://youtu.be/KkQ-1F0D0l0\">Watch the conversation</a>\r\n</strong></span><strong>Julie is featured at 29:25 on Accenture's commitment; 39:48 on supply chain transformation and 44:15 with advice for leaders. </strong>\r\n\r\nAs part of the historic 75th session of the UN General Assembly, <strong>CEO Julie Sweet</strong> was a featured speaker on the UN’s <a href=\"https://na.eventscloud.com/website/15648/home/\">Uniting Business LIVE</a>, a virtual forum of leaders from business, government and civil society convening to discuss and drive business ambition on the United Nations’ <a href=\"https://www.unglobalcompact.org/sdgs\">17 Sustainable Development Goals</a>, which cover issues such as inequality, poverty, education and climate—into their core business.\r\n\r\nJulie joined <strong>SAP CEO Christian Klein</strong> and <strong>3M CEO Mike Roman</strong> for a <a href=\"https://youtu.be/KkQ-1F0D0l0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>conversation</strong></a> moderated by <strong>Executive Director and CEO of the UN Global Compact Sanda Ojiambo</strong> about moving beyond incremental progress to transformation through SDG Ambition , our joint partnership with SAP and UN Global Compact, and most recently, 3M as Patron Sponsor, to challenge and support companies in integrating the 17 Sustainable Development Goals, which cover issues such as inequality, poverty, education and climate—into their core business.\r\n\r\nIn introducing the session, Ojiambo noted that “the business of business is truly no longer just business,” especially today.\r\n\r\n“The next few months provide a window of opportunity for all of us to make the seemingly impossible, possible. It's a time for reinvention, a time to reset, and a time for rebuilding to shape a sustainable future,’ she said. “For the private sector, this reinvention must address the wider societal and environmental impacts of business strategy in ways that drive both business benefit and societal transformation.”\r\n\r\nJulie expanded on the point, underscoring the role of technology.\r\n\r\n“If we think about it in the context of COVID, we need to accelerate digital because we are now in a remote, contactless world,” Julie said. “This is a once in a lifetime opportunity to re-platform global business through technology and change the business of business by building sustainability into the design.”\r\n\r\nTo do so, and to further accelerate business action in achieving the SDGs, the SDG Ambition program launched new guidance to provide business leaders with directional support on measuring and managing sustainability performance.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-3670 alignleft\" src=\"https://in.accenture.com/ceo/wp-content/uploads/sites/604/2020/09/SDG-Guide-233x300.jpg\" alt=\"Image of SDG Ambition Guide cover\" width=\"233\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"https://unglobalcompact.org/library/5791\"><strong>Ambition</strong> <strong>Guide: Setting Goals for the Decade of Action</strong></a> establishes the initial set of SDG Ambition Benchmarks that challenge organizations to set more ambitious goals and targets in the areas in which business is positioned to have a substantial impact.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><a href=\"https://unglobalcompact.org/library/5789\">Integration Guide: Designing Business Systems for the SDGs</a></strong> presents the approach through which the 10 SDG Ambition Benchmarks can be integrated into core business processes and systems to enable effective measurement and management of sustainability performance.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"https://unglobalcompact.org/library/5790\"><strong>SDG</strong> <strong>Ambition Benchmark Reference Sheets</strong></a> provide illustrative details regarding the steps to integrate each of these benchmarks into a company’s business systems, as well as the key design decision required to engage technology partners.</p>\r\n<strong>Collaborating with speed and humility </strong>\r\n\r\nJulie also shared how SDG Ambition underscores the humility and speed required when it comes to organizations working together.\r\n\r\n“To me, these collaborations demonstrate that we have to be humble and we have to learn from others,” she said. “Companies, governments and NGOs all have different perspectives and are doing great things, so having the humility to say we need to come together and learn from each other will give us the speed that is so critical to creating a better future.”\r\n\r\n<strong>What’s Next &amp; Learn More\r\n</strong>\r\nThrough the UN Global Compact and their Local Network teams, Accenture will be supporting the <strong>SDG Ambition Accelerator</strong> kicking off in January 2021. This program will guide 1,000+ companies, including many of our clients, in raising their sustainability ambitions and more deeply integrating the SDGs.  To learn more about the Accelerator, visit the <strong><a href=\"https://unglobalcompact.org/take-action/sdg-ambition\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">SDG Ambition website</a></strong>. To discuss applying SDG Ambition with your clients, please contact <strong>Michael D. Hughes</strong>.","post_link":"https://in.accenture.com/ceo/?site=1&blog=604&p=3657","site_url":"https://in.accenture.com/ceo/","post_thumb":"https://cdn.in.accenture.com/prod/wp-content/uploads/sites/604/2020/09/30165203/UN-Uniting-BUsiness-Live_800X480.jpg","post_date":"2020-09-30 17:54:02","post_modified":"2020-09-30 21:39:53","isread":"0","article_score":"214.399060","isfeatured":"0","source_short_tag":"Julie Here","category_url":"https://in.accenture.com/ceo/","source_url":"https://in.accenture.com/ceo"}],"sites":[{"aggregator_short_tag":"Trending","sitegrouporder":"1","short_tag":"India","site_url":"https://in.accenture.com/india/"},{"aggregator_short_tag":"Trending","sitegrouporder":"1","short_tag":"Growth Markets","site_url":"https://in.accenture.com/growthmarkets/"},{"aggregator_short_tag":"Location","sitegrouporder":"2","short_tag":"India","site_url":"https://in.accenture.com/india/"},{"aggregator_short_tag":"Organization","sitegrouporder":"3","short_tag":"Accenture Technology","site_url":"https://in.accenture.com/accenturetechnology/categories-news/"},{"aggregator_short_tag":"Global","sitegrouporder":"4","short_tag":"Across Accenture","site_url":"https://in.accenture.com/accenture/"},{"aggregator_short_tag":"Global","sitegrouporder":"4","short_tag":"Julie Here","site_url":"https://in.accenture.com/ceo/"}]}